<task id="027" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D2-17 Clickable citations (v1.1 `citations[].href`; v1.0 fallback)</title>
    <status>complete</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>~1.5h (sub-agent code-authoring scope; main session owns build, quality gates, commit, push)</actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started>2026-06-04</started>
    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration</phase>
    <wave>P2-G6 (parallel-safe within group; share `InsightsResponseRenderer` surface with tasks 024, 025, 026, 028)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>026 (D2-16 `InsightsResponseRenderer` two-path renderer exists; this task EXTENDS its citation rendering surface)</dependencies>
    <tags>frontend, insights, citations, v1.1</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend the Insights v1.1 chat-tool response renderer (`InsightsResponseRenderer`,
    produced by task 026) to render the `[n]` citation tokens in RAG-path and decline
    responses as clickable buttons WHEN the Insights v1.1 `citations[].href` field is
    populated. Clicking a clickable `[n]` MUST dispatch the EXISTING `context_update`
    event on the `context` PaneEventBus channel carrying the resolved URL as the
    payload; the existing `ContextPaneController` then resolves to the
    `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018), which opens the URL via iframe.

    The task ships THREE rendering scenarios for graceful v1.1/v1.0 + spike-outcome
    fallback per spec NFR-11 + UR-04:
      (a) **v1.1 with all `href` populated** (full clickable-citations UX);
      (b) **v1.1 with observation-only `href`** (Wave F spike-outcome contingency:
          document-citation `href` defers to v1.2; observation citations clickable,
          document citations render as display-name only);
      (c) **v1.0 with no `href` at all** (every citation renders display-name only,
          non-clickable; existing v1.0 behavior preserved).

    The task is **strictly additive frontend extension**: NO BFF code change, NO
    parallel preview surface (reuses `FilePreviewContextWidget` from task 018 via
    the existing `context_update` event channel), NO new PaneEventBus event type
    (the `context_update` discriminant already exists on the `context` channel per
    `PaneEventTypes.ts`). Per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4 + ADR-030: channel set stays at 4,
    event-type set on `context` channel includes the pre-existing
    `context_update` literal — this task DISPATCHES it; it does NOT add a new type.

    Per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.5 + spec NFR-11: v1.0 fallback MUST be silent (display-name
    only) — NO error UX when `href: null` or absent. Per the Insights team correction
    integrated into `notes/insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md` §0a: the URL
    in `citations[].href` resolves server-side via
    `DocumentCheckoutService.GetPreviewUrlAsync(driveId, itemId, ct)` on the Insights
    BFF side; R5 just consumes the pre-resolved URL string.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend engineer with Fluent UI v9 + React 19 expertise, familiarity
    with the existing `@spaarke/ai-widgets` PaneEventBus dispatch surface
    (`useDispatchPaneEvent`), the four-channel `PaneEventTypes` discriminated-union
    pattern (`workspace` / `context` / `chat` / `command`), the existing
    `context_update` event semantics consumed by `ContextPaneController.tsx`, and
    the `InsightsResponseRenderer` two-path rendering surface produced by task 026.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The `InsightsResponseRenderer` citation-rendering sub-component is extended so
    that all three scenarios (a/b/c) render correctly on Spaarke Dev. Specifically:
    (1) When a citation has a non-null `href`, `[n]` renders as a Fluent v9 `Button`
    (appearance="subtle" or "transparent", inline-friendly) with `onClick`
    dispatching `{ type: 'context_update', contextType: 'document', contextData:
    { url: citation.href, displayName: citation.source } }` to the `context`
    channel via `useDispatchPaneEvent`.
    (2) When a citation has `href: null` OR `href` is absent (v1.0 response or
    spike-outcome "observation-only-href"), `[n]` renders as a non-interactive
    `<span>` styled identically to its prior v1.0 appearance — display-name only;
    no button, no error.
    (3) The `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018) consumes the dispatched
    `context_update` event via its registered widget-resolution path
    (`ContextPaneController` → `ContextWidgetRegistry` lookup → `file-preview`
    widget type) and opens the URL in its iframe surface. Verification: click on
    `[n]` in the Insights renderer causes Context pane to render the source
    document inline.
    (4) Mixed-mode response (some citations have `href`, some don't) renders the
    clickable subset as buttons and the non-clickable subset as plain spans —
    no error, no rendering glitch.
    (5) `code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5.
    (6) BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (frontend-only change; confirmed in task notes).
  </goal>

