  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate">REUSE MANDATE — citation-click handler MUST dispatch the EXISTING `context_update` event on the EXISTING `context` PaneEventBus channel. MUST NOT add a parallel preview surface; the `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018) consumes the event via the existing `ContextPaneController` → `ContextWidgetRegistry` resolution path. MUST NOT introduce a new "open URL in iframe" component.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4">PaneEventBus channels are closed at 4 per ADR-030. The `context_update` literal already exists in `ContextPaneEvent.type` union (`'context_update' | 'context_highlight' | 'stage_change'` — verified in `PaneEventTypes.ts`). This task DISPATCHES it; it does NOT add a new event type.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.5">Insights tool integration governance — R5 NEVER injects Insights-internal types directly. R5 consumes the v1.1 contract via HTTP only. URL resolution happens server-side on the Insights BFF via `DocumentCheckoutService.GetPreviewUrlAsync(driveId, itemId, ct)` per Insights team correction (`insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md` §0a). R5 just consumes the pre-resolved URL string in `citations[].href`. NO frontend URL-construction logic.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-11">Back-compat for Insights consumption — R5 falls back gracefully to v1.0 (display-name only) if `href: null` or absent. UX is degraded but functional. NO error UX, NO console warnings, NO broken rendering. Mixed-mode (some `href` populated, some not) MUST render correctly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec UR-04">`citations[].href` schema-plumbing spike outcome — if Insights Wave F spike defers document-citation `href` to v1.2, R5 lives with observation-only `href` in v1.1 + display-name-only document citations. This task handles ALL THREE scenarios (a/b/c per &lt;goal&gt;) so that the spike outcome doesn't block R5 Phase 2.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens only — zero hard-coded hex/rgb. Dark-mode parity by construction. Clickable `[n]` MUST be a Fluent v9 `Button` (subtle/transparent appearance) styled inline-friendly so it doesn't break prose flow. Non-clickable `[n]` MUST be a `<span>` styled identically to its prior v1.0 appearance — no visual regression.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 functional components. Hooks only — `useDispatchPaneEvent` at component top level (NOT inside event handlers) per React 19 hook rules.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Code lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` (extends `InsightsResponseRenderer` produced by task 026). Component library boundaries respected.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">R5 introduces NO new feature flags. The clickable-citation behavior is unconditional (auto-detected from `href` presence per response payload).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">Additive event-type discipline — this task does NOT add a new event type; it DISPATCHES the existing `context_update` literal on the existing `context` channel. Existing subscribers (`ContextPaneController`) handle the event without modification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 / spec NFR-07">BFF publish-size — this task is frontend-only. Confirm `dotnet publish` delta = 0 MB in task notes. NO BFF code touched.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If task 026 produced a different citation payload shape than expected (e.g. `citations[].href` is named differently, or `source` is not the display name), surface the mismatch in task notes and request alignment with task 026 owner — do NOT silently rewrite the contract.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Mixed-mode rendering MUST be tested with a synthetic response payload (observation citation with `href`, document citation with `href: null`) — capture the verification in task notes.</constraint>
  </constraints>

