    <patterns>
      <pattern name="PaneEventBus dispatch (existing channel + event type)" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/useDispatchPaneEvent.ts">
        `const dispatch = useDispatchPaneEvent(); ... dispatch('context', { type: 'context_update', contextType: 'document', contextData: { url, displayName } });`. The `context_update` discriminant already exists in `ContextPaneEvent.type` (verified in `PaneEventTypes.ts`); this task DISPATCHES it. Hook MUST be called at component top level (React 19 hook rules), then the resulting `dispatch` function may be used inside `onClick` handlers.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="ContextPaneController consumption of context_update" location="src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/context/ContextPaneController.tsx">
        Existing flow: `usePaneEvent('context', ...)` handler matches `event.type === 'context_update'`, extracts `event.contextType` + `event.contextData`, resolves a widget via `ContextWidgetRegistry`, renders it. For the clickable-citation path: set `contextType = 'document'` (or whatever the registered `file-preview` widget keys off; verify against task 018's registration key); `contextData = { url, displayName }`. The `FilePreviewContextWidget` then opens the URL in its iframe surface.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Citation token rendering — clickable vs non-clickable" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/InsightsResponseRenderer.tsx">
        Extend the citation rendering loop produced by task 026. Pseudo-shape: `citations.map((c, i) =&gt; c.href ? &lt;Button appearance="subtle" inline onClick={() =&gt; dispatch('context', { type: 'context_update', contextType: 'document', contextData: { url: c.href, displayName: c.source }})}&gt;[{i+1}]&lt;/Button&gt; : &lt;span&gt;[{i+1}]&lt;/span&gt;)`. Use Fluent v9 `Button` for clickable; styled inline (no block-level layout disruption). Use plain `&lt;span&gt;` for non-clickable. Both share the same `[n]` visual baseline (font-size, color tokens) so the response prose flow is uniform.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Mixed-mode rendering tolerance" location="N/A — design pattern">
        Citations array may contain a mix of `href`-populated and `href: null` entries (Wave F spike-outcome scenario b). The map MUST evaluate `c.href` per entry — no all-or-nothing rendering decision at the array level.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="No URL construction on client" location="notes/insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md §0a">
        Per Insights team correction integrated into the v1.1 negotiation outcome: the URL in `citations[].href` is pre-resolved server-side via `DocumentCheckoutService.GetPreviewUrlAsync(driveId, itemId, ct)` on the Insights BFF. R5 frontend does NOT construct, sign, augment, or transform the URL. It is passed through verbatim to the dispatched event payload.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 Phase 2 consumes the Insights Engine v1.1 chat-tool contract via the
      `insights.query` agent-tool (task 024). Responses arrive in two shapes
      (playbook / RAG) with a `citations[]` array on RAG and decline paths. The
      v1.0 contract carries `Source string` only — citations appear in prose as
      `[n]` tokens that the user cannot click to verify. The v1.1 negotiation
      added optional `citations[].href` so the chat agent can render `[n]` as
      a clickable button that opens the source in the Context pane via the
      existing `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018). This task ships that
      clickable-button UX, with graceful fallback for v1.0 + the Wave F
      spike-outcome contingency (document-citation `href` deferred to v1.2;
      observation-only-href scenario per `insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md`
      §0a). The dispatching mechanism is the existing `context_update` event on
      the existing `context` PaneEventBus channel — same path used by entity-info
      / citation-highlight / sources-citations widgets today. The
      `FilePreviewContextWidget` produced by task 018 is the consumer; this
      task wires the producer (citation click → dispatch).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="026" status="not-started">
        Task 026 (D2-16) produces the two-path `InsightsResponseRenderer` with
        a citation-rendering sub-component. This task EXTENDS that sub-component
        with the clickable-button logic + dispatch wiring. If task 026 has not
        landed, this task is blocked.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 018 (D2-09) `FilePreviewContextWidget` is the consumer of the
        dispatched `context_update` event. Task 018 must be landed for the
        click path to render a preview; otherwise the dispatch happens but the
        Context pane renders its default empty/spinner state (the path is still
        not broken — degraded gracefully).</item>
      <item>Task 024 (D2-14) registers `InsightsQueryToolHandler` and produces
        the response payload that feeds `InsightsResponseRenderer`. Task 027
        consumes `citations[].href` if it's populated.</item>
      <item>Task 028 (D2-18) adds the confidence-floor badge to the same
        `InsightsResponseRenderer` surface. Parallel-safe with this task —
        different sub-components, no overlap.</item>
      <item>Task 029 (D2-19) handles the 12 Insights error codes. Independent
        from this task (error-code rendering is a separate sub-component).</item>
      <item>Spec UR-04 + NFR-11 + design.md §4.12 — this task is the load-bearing
        implementation of the "v1.1 graceful fallback" claim.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

