      (a) the task-026 output `InsightsResponseRenderer.tsx` — locate the
      citation-rendering sub-component + verify the payload shape it consumes
      (citations array structure, field names, `source` vs `displayName`, etc.);
      (b) `PaneEventTypes.ts` `ContextPaneEvent` union — confirm `context_update`
      literal is present + payload field names (`contextType`, `contextData`);
      (c) `ContextPaneController.tsx` `context_update` handler — verify the
      `contextType` value the `file-preview` widget keys off (cross-check
      against task 018's registry key `'file-preview'`);
      (d) `insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md` §0a — confirm
      `citations[].href` semantics + the three scenarios (a/b/c per &lt;goal&gt;).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Plan Implementation">
      Decompose into sub-tasks:
      (a) Locate the citation-rendering sub-component in `InsightsResponseRenderer.tsx`
          (produced by task 026);
      (b) Add `useDispatchPaneEvent` hook at top of the containing component
          (React 19 hook rules);
      (c) Implement per-citation conditional rendering: `c.href ? &lt;Button&gt; :
          &lt;span&gt;`;
      (d) Wire `onClick` handler on the `Button` to dispatch
          `context_update` event with `{ url, displayName }` payload;
      (e) Verify mixed-mode rendering (some `href`, some `null`) — no
          all-or-nothing decision at the array level;
      (f) Confirm v1.0 (no `href` at all) → all `&lt;span&gt;` rendering, no
          errors, no console warnings;
      (g) Visual styling — match prior v1.0 `[n]` appearance for non-clickable
          spans; Fluent v9 `Button` subtle/transparent inline for clickable;
      (h) Dark-mode verification.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Clickable-Button Branch (scenario a)">
      In the citation-rendering sub-component, add the clickable branch.
      Pseudo-shape:
      ```tsx
      const dispatch = useDispatchPaneEvent();
      // ... within citation map:
      citations.map((c, i) =&gt; {
        const label = `[${i + 1}]`;
        if (c.href) {
          return (
            &lt;Button
              key={i}
              appearance="subtle"
              size="small"
              onClick={() =&gt; dispatch('context', {
                type: 'context_update',
                contextType: 'document',
                contextData: { url: c.href, displayName: c.source },
              })}
              className={styles.citationButton}
            &gt;{label}&lt;/Button&gt;
          );
        }
        // Fall through to scenario (b)/(c) span branch in Step 5
      });
      ```
      Use Fluent v9 semantic tokens for the button (no hex/rgb). Verify
      `contextType: 'document'` matches the registry key consumed by
      `ContextPaneController` for the `file-preview` widget (cross-check
      against task 018 + `register-context-widgets.ts` registration).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Implement Non-Clickable Span Branch (scenarios b + c)">
      Add the non-clickable branch for `href: null` OR `href` absent:
      ```tsx
      return &lt;span key={i} className={styles.citationLabel}&gt;{label}&lt;/span&gt;;
      ```
      Style the span to match prior v1.0 `[n]` visual (font-size, color tokens
      identical to clickable button's text). Confirm v1.0 (no `href` field at
      all in payload) → JavaScript truthiness check `c.href` evaluates to
      `false`/`undefined` → renders span (no `TypeError`, no console warning).
      Confirm scenario (b) "observation-only-href" — citations array contains
      mix of `href`-populated (observation citations) and `href: null`
      (document citations) — renders correctly per-entry.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify Mixed-Mode Rendering With Synthetic Payload">
      Build a synthetic test payload covering all three scenarios:
      ```ts
      // Scenario (a) — all href populated
      const v11Full = { citations: [
        { source: 'Matter Engagement Letter', href: 'https://.../api/v1/documents/abc/preview' },
        { source: 'Invoice #12345', href: 'https://.../api/v1/documents/def/preview' },
      ]};
      // Scenario (b) — observation-only href (spike-outcome contingency)
      const v11Partial = { citations: [
        { source: 'Matter observation', href: 'https://.../api/insights/observation/xyz' },
        { source: 'Document — Engagement Letter', href: null },
      ]};
      // Scenario (c) — v1.0 (no href at all)
      const v10 = { citations: [
        { source: 'Matter Engagement Letter' },
        { source: 'Invoice #12345' },
      ]};
      ```
      Render each via Storybook or test harness; verify:
      - (a) two Buttons, both clickable, both dispatch on click;
      - (b) one Button (observation) + one span (document); only the Button
            dispatches;
      - (c) two spans; neither dispatches; no console warnings/errors.
      Capture the verification (screenshots or assertion log) in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify FilePreviewContextWidget Consumption">
      With task 018 already landed (or stubbed if not), verify the end-to-end
      click-to-preview flow on Spaarke Dev (or a local SpaarkeAi shell):
      (a) trigger an Insights query that returns v1.1 RAG response with `href`;
      (b) click `[1]` in the Workspace tab's `InsightsResponseRenderer` output;
      (c) confirm `ContextPaneController` receives the `context_update` event
          (browser devtools — PaneEventBus subscription firing);
      (d) confirm Context pane switches to `FilePreviewContextWidget` rendering
