  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`InsightsResponseRenderer.tsx` is extended such that citation `[n]` tokens render as a Fluent v9 `Button` (subtle/transparent appearance) WHEN `citations[i].href` is non-null/non-undefined, and as a plain `&lt;span&gt;` otherwise.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Clicking a clickable `[n]` Button dispatches an event to the `context` PaneEventBus channel with shape `{ type: 'context_update', contextType: 'document', contextData: { url: citations[i].href, displayName: citations[i].source } }` via `useDispatchPaneEvent` — verified by inspecting the dispatch in browser devtools / a test harness assertion.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Scenario (a) — v1.1 response with all `href` populated — every citation renders as a clickable Button; clicking opens the source URL in the Context pane via `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018) consuming the dispatched event.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Scenario (b) — v1.1 response with observation-only `href` (UR-04 spike-outcome contingency) — observation citations render as Buttons (clickable); document citations render as `&lt;span&gt;` (display-name only); no console errors or warnings; mixed-mode rendering works correctly per-entry.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Scenario (c) — v1.0 response with no `href` at all — every citation renders as `&lt;span&gt;` (display-name only); no error UX; no broken rendering; `[n]` visual matches prior v1.0 appearance (no regression).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018) consumes the dispatched `context_update` event and renders the source URL in its iframe surface — end-to-end click-to-preview verified on Spaarke Dev (or documented as deferred if task 018 is not yet ✅, with the dispatch itself verified independently).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NO new PaneEventBus event type is added by this task (the `context_update` literal already exists in `ContextPaneEvent.type` per `PaneEventTypes.ts`) — verified by diff against `PaneEventTypes.ts` (no edits to that file by this task).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NO new PaneEventBus channel is added (channel set remains the closed 4 per ADR-030 + R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4) — verified by absence of new channel registration code.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NO new feature flag introduced; clickable-citation behavior is auto-detected from `href` presence per response payload — verified by absence of `if (flag)` blocks in modified files.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Dark-mode parity verified by toggling SpaarkeAi shell theme; no hard-coded hex/rgb appears in the modified files (regex audit: no `#[0-9a-fA-F]{3,8}` or `rgb(` outside Fluent token references).</criterion>
